PHASE COUNT GUIDANCE
====================================================
The number of phases MUST reflect the concept's actual documentation lifecycle. Different concepts have fundamentally different lifecycles.

A phase is justified ONLY when it introduces a meaningfully different combination of authors, documents, settings, or signals. If two moments in time involve the same people writing the same documents at the same place about the same signals — that is one phase, not two.

Conversely, do NOT compress distinct documentation stages into fewer phases. If a concept genuinely passes through 5 different clinical stages with different documentation patterns, return 5 phases.

