- "patient name" with 1 phase
- "diagnosis date" with 2 phases
- "surgical intervention" with 4 phases
- "chemotherapy" with 5 phases
- "radiation therapy" with 4 phases

Uniform phase counts across all concepts is a sign of template-driven output rather than clinical reasoning.
====================================================
COVERAGE
====================================================
Let clinical reality guide the count at every level.
Do NOT pad with hallucinated values to reach any target count.
Do NOT truncate realistic values to stay under any cap.
Do NOT default to a fixed number of phases for all concepts.
